<div style="padding: 10px 30px">
    <h3>Java Core</h3>
<p><strong>The Java Core quest</strong> is intended for those who have already received basic <strong>Java</strong> training (by completing <strong>Code<span class="text-corporate">Gym</span>'s Java Syntax quest</strong>). Here you have to pass <strong>10 fascinating levels</strong> where you will learn the basics of <strong>OOP</strong>, get acquainted with streams, serialization, and method overloading, and you'll learn a lot about interfaces and multiple inheritance. The training is no longer as simple as the <strong>Java Syntax quest</strong>, but regular practice (by completing tasks) will help you pass all <strong>10 levels</strong> in this quest, and you'll be ready to complete mini-projects in the near future.</p>
